---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Harmonium from '../../components/Harmonium.astro';
---
<Layout title="Reading Sargam Notation | Harmonium Halt"
  description="Learn to read and write sargam notation — India's elegant system for writing music. Free harmonium lesson with interactive web harmonium tool.">
  <div class="bg-white border-b" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <a href="/lessons">Lessons</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <span>Reading Sargam Notation</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-beginner capitalize">beginner</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.4);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">⏱ 20 min · Lesson 6 of 8</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="section-title text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Reading Sargam Notation</h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.6);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Learn to read and write sargam notation — India's elegant system for writing music.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-5 mb-6 border" style="background:#fef9f0;border-color:rgba(212,146,10,.25)">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-sm mb-3" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">📌 Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>S R G M P D N = the 7 natural swaras in notation</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Underline or lowercase = komal: r g d n</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Apostrophe or accent = Tivra Ma: M'</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Dot below = Mandra (lower octave), dot above = Taar</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Vertical line = beat boundary in rhythmic notation</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-hm">
      <h2>The Sargam Notation System</h2>
      <p>Sargam uses the first letter of each swara name as its written symbol: S R G M P D N. These letters are written in sequence to show a melody with special marks indicating octave and whether a swara is komal or tivra. It is simple yet expressive working for any instrument in any key.</p>

      <h2>Octave and Alteration Markers</h2>
      <p>In Mandra (lower) octave place a dot below: dot-S dot-R. In Madhya (middle) octave write plain letters: S R G M P D N. In Taar (upper) octave place a dot above. For komal write underline or use lowercase: r g d n. For Tivra Ma write M' or M with accent. Combining these markers covers all 36 notes across three octaves.</p>

      <h2>Reading Your First Notation</h2>
      <p>Here is the ascending scale of Raga Yaman: N R G M' P D N S-dot-above. Reading left to right: Ni natural, Re, Ga, Tivra Ma, Pa, Dha, Ni, then Taar Sa. Notice the scale starts from Ni below Sa — a characteristic movement of Yaman. Practice playing exactly this notated sequence.</p>

      <h2>Rhythm in Sargam Notation</h2>
      <p>Notes separated by spaces get equal time. A comma indicates a pause or breath. A dash after a note means hold it longer. Two notes written together with no space are played quickly. Vertical lines separate beat divisions. A bold vertical line marks the start of the taal cycle (Sam). With these symbols any melody can be precisely notated.</p>

      <h2>Writing Practice</h2>
      <p>Practice writing these notations yourself: 1) Full ascending scale: S R G M P D N S. 2) Bhairavi aroha: S r g M P d n S. 3) Yaman pakad: N R G comma M' G R S. Writing notation while playing reinforces both the visual and physical understanding of the notes simultaneously.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Practice Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-4" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Apply what you just learned on the interactive harmonium below.</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c1008,#3d1a08)">
        <Harmonium/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-stretch xs:items-center justify-between gap-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
      <a href="/lessons" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;text-decoration:none">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        All Lessons
      </a>
      <a href="/practice" class="btn-primary justify-center text-center">Open Full Practice Tool →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>